                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d236">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">715.1715/1450: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Erwin</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-07-18T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 18, 1939—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>18. For Ocheltree. Your No. 10, July 17, 5 p.m. Authorization granted for
                    stopover in San Salvador to make presentation to Dr. Lainez, but before leaving
                    Tegucigalpa you should satisfy yourself that this action will be entirely
                    agreeable to the Honduran Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
